label.value: larval Pdf neuron close to calyx

value.value: Larval Pdf (FBgn0023178) expressing interneuron whose cell body lies in a cluster within the dorsal cortex. Pdf expression begins late in L1. Its process project into the median ventral brain dorsolateral to the esophagus. There are two to four of these neurons per cluster.

definition.value: Helfrich-Forster (1997) notes that the Pdf staining is faint and is only visible in 50% of examined larval brains.

label.value: larval Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere

value.value: Pdf-expressing neuron whose cell body is located in a ventral cluster in the eighth larval abdominal neuromere of the ventral ganglion. There are 8 of these per cluster - each projecting though the paired eighth abdominal nerve to the posterior end of the larva (Helfrich-Forster, 1997). They are glutamatergic motor neurons that arborize over the posterior end of the hindgut, with refined branches and abundant bouton structures (Zhang et al., 2014).

label.value: extra LNd neuron

value.value: LNd neuron of the adult brain characterized by having a slightly larger nucleus and cytoplasmic area compared to the other LNd neurons.

definition.value: Rieger et al. (2006) comment that the extra LNd also stains more strongly for Period (FBgn0003068) and Timeless (FBgn0014396) compared to the other LNd neurons. Under constant light (LL) conditions, the extra LNd neuron is the only LNd neuron which shows significant Period and Timeless cycling. This neuron must belong to one of the other LNd subclasses. It is most likely equivalent to the ITP and CRY expressing LNd neuron, as this has the largest cell diameter among LNd neurons (Schubert et al., 2018 - FBrf0238313).

label.value: adult Pdf neuron

value.value: Pdf expressing neuron that is part of the adult.

label.value: pupal Pdf neuron

value.value: Pdf expressing neuron that is part of the pupa.

label.value: pupal s-LNv Pdf neuron

value.value: Pupal s-LNv that expresses Pdf (FBgn0023178). There are four of these per cluster of pupal s-LNv neurons.

label.value: pupal l-LNv Pdf neuron

value.value: Pdf (FBgn0023178) neuron of the pupal period-expressing LNv cluster with a large cell body and generally located more dorsally than the s-LNv neurons. These cells begin to express Pdf at approximately 50% of pupal development.

label.value: pupal Pdf neuron close to calyx

value.value: Neuron of the pupa that is located dorsoanterior to the calyx of the mushroom body and that expresses Pdf (FBgn0023178).

label.value: pupal Pdf neuron close to tritocerebrum

value.value: Pupal Pdf expressing neuron whose soma is located in a cluster antero-ventral the tritocerebrum. There are 2-4 of these per cluster.

label.value: larval s-LNv neuron

value.value: Larval neuron of the period-expressing LNv cluster, with a small cell body. These neurons innervate the larval optic neuropil (Larderet et al., 2017) and are thought to develop into the adult s-LNv neurons (Kaneko et al., 1997). There are 5 cells present in each cluster, all except one of which express Pdf (FBgn0023178).

definition.value: This appears to be the only type of lateral period neuron in the larva (Kaneko et al., 1997), so this term may be equivalent to FBbt:00001913 'larval LN period neuron' - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.

label.value: larval Pdf negative s-LNv neuron

value.value: Larval s-LNv neuron that does not express Pdf (FBgn0023178). It innervates the larval optic neuropil significantly and projects to a broader domain than the four Pdf positive s-LNv neurons (Keene et al., 2011), including the lateral horn and mushroom body accessory calyx (Larderet et al., 2017). There is only one of these cells per hemisphere and it is cholinergic (Larderet et al., 2017).

label.value: pupal s-LNv neuron

value.value: Neuron of the pupal period-expressing LNv cluster with a small cell body and generally located more dorsally than the l-LNv neurons. There are 5 cells present in each cluster, all except one of which express Pdf (FBgn0023178).

label.value: pupal Pdf negative s-LNv neuron

value.value: Pupal s-LNv neuron that does not express Pdf (FBgn0023178) (Kaneko et al., 1997). There is only one of these per ventral cluster of LN period neurons.

label.value: small larval Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere

value.value: Larval Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a smaller cell body than the large Pdf neurons that are located more ventral and anteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label.value: large larval Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere

value.value: Larval Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a larger cell body than the small Pdf neurons that are located more posteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label.value: small adult Pdf neuron of abdominal segment

value.value: Adult Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a smaller cell body than the large Pdf neurons that are located more ventral and anteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label.value: large adult Pdf neuron of abdominal neuromere

value.value: Adult Pdf neuron of the abdominal neuromere with a larger cell body than the small Pdf neurons that are located more posteriorly (Helfrich-Forster, 1997).

label.value: pupal LN period neuron

value.value: Laterally located period (FBgn0003068) expressing neuron of the pupal brain.

label.value: pupal DN period neuron

value.value: A Per (FBgn0003068) expressing neuron that is located in a dorsoanterior cluster in the pupal brain.

label.value: pupal DN1 period neuron

value.value: Neuron of the DN1 cluster, that is located dorsal to the DN2 cluster at 70% pupal development. There are around 7 neurons in this cluster.

label.value: pupal DN2 period neuron

value.value: Neuron of the DN2 cluster, that is located ventral to the DN2 cluster at 70% pupal development. There are between 1-2 neurons in this cluster.

label.value: pupal DN3 period neuron

value.value: Neuron of the DN3 cluster, that is located lateral to the DN1 and DN2 clusters at 70% pupal development. There are around 16 neurons in this cluster.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of mechanosensory medial triple row bristle

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a medial triple row bristle.

label.value: chemosensory dorsal double row bristle

value.value: Multiply innervated, recurved chemosensory bristle of the dorsal row of double row wing sensilla (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

definition.value: Palka et al. (1979) show that of the five dendrites innervating the wing margin chemosensory bristles, one contains a microtubular body, suggesting it to be a mechanosensory neuron. That this bristle is chemosensory in nature is based on the presence of the terminal pore and multiple innervation with dendrites extending to the pore (Palka et al., 1979).

label.value: mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle

value.value: Slender, singly-innervated mechanosensory bristle of the dorsal row of double row wing sensilla (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

definition.value: That this bristle is mechanosensory is primarily based on the presence of a characteristic microtubular body present in the single innervating neuron (Palka et al., 1979).

label.value: chemosensory neuron of dorsal double row bristle

value.value: Chemosensory neuron that has its dendrite in a bristle of the dorsal double row.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of chemosensory dorsal double row bristle

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates a chemosensory dorsal double row bristle.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates a mechanosensory dorsal double row bristle.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of chemosensory ventral double row bristle

value.value: Neuron involved in mechanosensation that is a part of the ventral double row chemosensory bristles.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of chemosensory ventral triple row bristle

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a chemosensory ventral triple row bristle.

label.value: larval LNd neuron

value.value: Larval neuron of the period-expressing LNd cluster, whose soma is located in the dorsal lateral brain.

definition.value: Possible candidate for obsoletion: cited reference does not show existence of LNd neurons in larvae - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.

label.value: adult period glial cell

value.value: Period (FBgn0003068) expressing glial cell.

label.value: cell body rind region

value.value: A subdivision of the cell body rind of the central nervous system. It includes the neuronal cell bodies.

definition.value: Ito et al. (2014) may further subdivide cortex/rind regions into multiple facets. Subdivisions should be denoted by the addition of a single letter body-axis direction, e.g. rLHa for anterior to the lateral horn; rSMPm for medial to the superior medial protocerebrum, etc.

label.value: adult lateral brain cell body rind

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind found in the area between the central brain and the optic lobe (Ito et al., 2014). It includes the regions lateral to the anterior optic tubercle, superior lateral protocerebrum (pars lateralis), lateral horn, ventrolateral protocerebrum, wedge, saddle, inferior posterior slope and posterior lateral protocerebrum (Ito et al., 2014).

label.value: cell body rind of adult superior lateral protocerebrum

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the superior lateral protocerebrum.

label.value: cell body rind of adult posterior lateral protocerebrum

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the posterior lateral protocerebrum.

label.value: cell body rind of adult superior medial protocerebrum

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the superior medial protocerebrum.

label.value: cell body rind of adult medulla

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the medulla.

label.value: cell body rind of adult lamina

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the lamina.

label.value: cell body rind of adult lobula

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the lobula.

label.value: cell body rind of adult anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label.value: cell body rind of adult gnathal ganglion

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the gnathal ganglion.

label.value: cell body rind of adult antennal lobe

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the antennal lobe.

label.value: cell body rind of adult posterior slope

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the posterior slope.

label.value: cell body rind of adult inferior neuropils

value.value: Region of the adult brain cell body rind that overlies the inferior neuropils.

label.value: dopaminergic PAM neuron

value.value: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 100 cell bodies in the cortex of the anterior inferior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain (Mao and Davis, 2009). There are 15 types, of which most (but not all) target the medial lobe (Li et al., 2020). They all follow a mushroom body commissure to the contralateral mushroom body (Li et al., 2020). They are secondary neurons, with some belonging to the CREa1A (BAMd1A) hemilineage and some belonging to the CREa2A (DALcm1A) hemilineage (Lee et al., 2020; Truman et al., 2023).

definition.value: The cluster of PAM neurons was judged by a curator to correspond to the AM cell cluster in Budnik and White (1988).

label.value: dopaminergic PAL neuron

value.value: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 5 cell bodies in the cortex located lateral to the dorsal portion of the vertical lobes in the middle of the superior lateral protocerebrum of the adult brain.

definition.value: Mao and Davis (2009) identify 8 protocerebral clusters coincidentally positive for TH-GAL4 activity and tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactivity, implying these cells are dopaminergic.

label.value: dopaminergic PPM1 neuron

value.value: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a small cluster along the dorsoventral midline of the posterior superior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain.

definition.value: Mao and Davis (2009) identify 8 protocerebral clusters coincidentally positive for TH-GAL4 activity and tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactivity, implying these cells are dopaminergic. They refer to the protocerebral posteriomedial dopaminergic neuron 1 as a cluster.

label.value: dopaminergic PPM2 neuron

value.value: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster of approximately 8 cell bodies in the cortex of the posterior inferior medial protocerebrum of the adult brain (Mao and Davis, 2009). Different subtypes develop from the DM2, DM3 and DM4 neuroblasts (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: Mao and Davis (2009) identify 8 protocerebral clusters coincidentally positive for TH-GAL4 activity and tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactivity, implying these cells are dopaminergic. The cluster of PPM2 neurons was judged by a curator to correspond to the DM cell cluster in Budnik and White (1988).

label.value: dopaminergic PPM3 neuron

value.value: A dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in a cluster in the cortex of the superior posterior slope of the adult brain (Mao and Davis, 2009). There are approximately 8-9 of these cells and their axons project along the medial equatorial fascicle to the central complex and adjacent neuropil regions (Omoto et al., 2018). It develops from the DM6 neuroblast during the larval stage (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: Mao and Davis (2009) identify 8 protocerebral clusters coincidentally positive for TH-GAL4 activity and tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactivity, implying these cells are dopaminergic. The cluster of PPM3 neurons was judged by a curator to correspond to the PM cell cluster in Budnik and White (1988).
